      <h1>Chapter History</h1>
    
      <p>As one of the oldest Delta Chi Fraternity chapters west of the Mississippi and the oldest in the state of Missouri, the University of Missouri chapter has a storied history that spans over half a century back to our chapter founding on April 21, 1951.</p> 
      <p>The Fraternity that was founded at Cornell University in Ithaca, New York, with the principles of the promotion of friendship and brotherhood, the development of character for young collegiate men, the advancement of justice, and to provide assistance for young collegiate men in the acquisition of their education took root in the hearts of the 26 young undergraduate men who today are recognized as the founders of the University of Missouri Chapter:</p>
